# Changelog

## Unreleased

- Implemented `ModalClient` satisfying `GenerationClient` Protocol in `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/client_modal.py`, enabling CypherClaw to use Modal serverless for generation (CCG-012). The client computes A10G runtime cost from metadata and gracefully degrades when the `modal` SDK is not installed. Also added protocol parity tests and gated live Modal tests behind `--run-live-modal`.

- Added a manifest-driven CCS-032 library migration path: `my-claw/tools/sample_library_import.py` now imports single files and directory buckets into `samples/library/`, `senseweave.sample_library.SampleRecord` / `SampleLibrary` now preserve full-record provenance via serialized record storage (including `extras.original_path` and `extras.captured_by`), `tests/test_sample_library_import.py` locks the importer contract, `sample_manifests/anthony-library.toml` captures Anthony's real 101-sample migration plan, and the resulting local library import is kept out of git via `.gitignore`.
- Added the missing CCS-028 sample-usage journal seam for tracker pieces: `senseweave.usage_journal` now serializes the richer per-piece sampler fields (`started_at`, `mode`, `samples_used`, `transformations`, `clicks`) while preserving the legacy `timestamp` / `samples_played` aliases, `music_tracker_runtime.ScheduledTrackerEvent` now carries sample-gesture metadata through playback emission, `duet_composer.py` now records actual emitted sample-lane events into the post-piece journal hook, and new regression coverage in `tests/test_usage_journal.py`, `tests/test_music_tracker_runtime.py`, and `tests/test_usage_journal_integration.py` composes a short score-tree piece end to end and proves the written journal entry contains populated sample usage, transformations, and arc payoff data.
- Added focused regression coverage for the operator-diagnostics sampler line (`OperatorDiagnostics.sample_source`) in `tests/test_operator_diagnostics_sample_status.py`, pinning the four discrete states the formatter must produce: sampling-only renders `currently sampling …` without a playback fragment, playing-only renders `playing sample …` without a sampling fragment, both-active joins the two phrases with ` · `, and the all-idle case degrades to `unavailable` so the daemon never serializes an empty sampler line.
- Added a repo-backed `inkplate_display.py` renderer seam for the sampler status surface: it reuses `senseweave.sample_status.face_display_sample_status_text(...)` so the e-ink display follows the same combined plan+playback wording as the face display, and it truncates long sampler lines against the configured e-ink text width with Pillow-based measurement plus `...` instead of letting them overflow. Added regression coverage in `tests/test_inkplate_display.py` for helper wiring, width-fit truncation, fit-without-truncation, and empty-state degradation.
- Wired the combined sampler plan+playback status line into the face display renderer so the small face monitor mirrors operator diagnostics: added `senseweave.sample_status.face_display_sample_status_text(...)` as a thin wrapper that opts into `combine_activity_and_playback=True`, and updated `my-claw/tools/face_display.py` to call it in place of the legacy either/or `sample_status_text(...)` while preserving the existing 24pt centered placement and degradation guards. Coverage in `tests/test_face_display_sample_status.py` pins the combined wording, plan-only fallback, monitor-offline degradation, and the renderer call site.
- Operator `/status` sampler diagnostics now combine sampler plan and active playback into one human-readable line when both `/tmp/sample_dsp_activity.json` and `/tmp/sample_playback_state.json` are present, while leaving the face-display sampler wording on its existing playback-first contract; added regression coverage in `tests/test_operator_diagnostics.py`, `tests/test_sample_status.py`, and `tests/test_musical_integration_runtime.py`.
- Wired active-song human phrase capture into the live listeners: new `senseweave.phrase_capture_runtime.ActiveSongPhraseCapture` gates `PhraseCaptureWriter` on fresh `/tmp/composer_state.json` song context, `midi_keyboard_listener.py` and `theramini_listener.py` now feed qualifying >5s phrases into `samples/keyboard/` and `samples/theramini/` with validated song/key/tempo sidecars, `PhraseCaptureWriter` now exposes `reset()` for safe song-boundary drops, and `human_phrase_capture_verify.py` plus new runtime/integration tests simulate both sources without hardware and validate the resulting paths and tags.
- Added a piece-aware sampler cast-planning seam: `senseweave.cast_planner` now exposes `assemble_cast(...)`, which derives selector kwargs from a piece fixture (`mode`, `arc_phase`, `mood`, `target_character`/`patch_name`), returns assembled cast entries, and mirrors any pre-selected sampler summary onto the sampler cast entry as `sample_record`; sampler summaries now also derive `duration_sec` from capture-shaped records via `frame_count / sample_rate`, and `duet_composer._get_cast()` now routes through the shared cast assembler. Added regression coverage in `tests/test_cast_planner.py` for fixture-piece planning and capture-shaped sample summaries, while keeping the targeted `cast_planner` + `sampler_dispatch` suites green.
- Added `my-claw/tools/sample_capture_service_verify.py` plus `tests/test_sample_capture_service_verify.py` as a repo-backed operational verifier for `cypherclaw-sample-capture.service`: it checks `active/running` state, confirms the `cypherclaw-jack.service` dependency, and proves `Restart=always` recovery by forcing a `kill -9` and waiting for a new PID. Verified live on `cypherclaw` on April 25, 2026 with the daemon restarting from PID `1677354` to `1719358`.
- Deployed `cypherclaw-sample-capture.service` to the live CypherClaw host: installed the repo-backed unit at `/etc/systemd/system/cypherclaw-sample-capture.service`, ran `systemctl daemon-reload`, then `systemctl enable --now cypherclaw-sample-capture.service`. The service is now `enabled` and `active (running)` under systemd supervision with its `cypherclaw-jack.service` dependency satisfied, so `sample_capture_daemon.py` survives reboots and crash restarts without manual intervention.
- Added repo-backed sample-capture service wiring for the sampler rollout: `my-claw/systemd/cypherclaw-sample-capture.service` now runs `sample_capture_daemon.py` as `User=user` from the project virtualenv with `Restart=always`, `LimitMEMLOCK=infinity`, and `After`/`Requires` on `cypherclaw-jack.service`; `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now best-effort starts that service after the AV stack comes up; and `tests/test_cypherclaw_boot_runtime.py` pins both the unit-file contract and the boot-script hook.
- Added `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-artistic-intent.md` as the missing CCS-033 companion page: it states the sampler's aesthetic goals, names the three core usages (memory of place, self-quotation, curated found-sound library), explains `sw_sampler` as the quintet's memory voice, and defines the intended listener experience plus the five governing principles without duplicating implementation detail; added `tests/test_cypherclaw_sampler_artistic_intent.py` to pin the document's required sections, artistic concepts, concise length, and sampler-doc cross-links, and linked the new page from the sampler architecture doc and the musicianship roadmap.
- Added `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-architecture.md` to fill the gap between the sampler PRD and the musicianship roadmap: it lists the landed sampler components (`sample_capture_daemon.py`, `sample_capture_verify.py`, `sampler_buffers.py`, `sampler_dispatch.py`, `synthesis/sampler_effects.scd`, `render/antipatterns.py`), traces the end-to-end signal flow from JACK input through capture, tagging, `index.sqlite`, dispatch, the `sw_sampler_fx` bus, and the master bus, names both live anti-pattern detectors (`sampler_dominating`, `sampler_silent_quintet_member`), enumerates integration seams (identity, cast planner, mix engine, composer, operator diagnostics), and explicitly flags `SampleLibrary`, `SampleSelector`, `sw_sampler.scd`, and quintet identity convergence as still pending; `tests/test_cypherclaw_sampler_architecture.py` pins the doc's required sections, the referenced file paths, and the live anti-pattern names so future renames or section drops force the doc to update with the code.
- Updated `docs/cypherclaw-musicianship-roadmap.md` to describe the active quintet direction: `sw_bell_warm`, `sw_bowed`, `sw_breath`, `sw_pad`, and the new `sw_sampler` memory voice; the roadmap now separates landed sampler modules (`sample_capture_daemon.py`, `sampler_buffers.py`, `sampler_dispatch.py`, `sampler_effects.scd`, anti-pattern checks) from still-pending identity/library/SynthDef convergence so the documentation matches the tree's real partial-rollout state.
- Wired sample auto-tagging into the capture write path: `sample_capture_daemon.py` now exposes a stdlib-only `save_capture()` helper that writes mono 24-bit WAV captures, emits contextual + acoustic tags via `build_sample_tags()`, and persists both flattened tag fields and JSON payloads into `index.sqlite`; `tests/test_sample_capture_daemon.py` now covers room/contextual tag emission, sample-index persistence, and percussive contact-capture indexing.
- Closed the server-side gap on the new master-bus sampler controls: added a `master_smooth.scd` SuperCollider source stub for `sw_master_smooth` that declares `sampler_amp` and `sampler_bypass_comp` (both default 1.0) alongside the existing `amp` / `drive` / `warmth` / `reverb` / `room` surface; refactored `start_audio.sh` and `restart_composer.sh` to seed the master node via `senseweave.master_bus.master_bus_s_new_args()` so the boot-time `/s_new sw_master_smooth` arg list stays in lockstep with `DEFAULT_MASTER_BUS_VALUES`; added `tests/test_master_smooth_scd.py` to pin the stub's control declarations and the boot scripts' helper-driven seeding.
- Hardened sampler buffer cap enforcement: `BufferLoader` now rejects non-positive capacities, routes overflow eviction through `on_sampler_free()` before issuing new `/b_alloc` + `/b_allocRead` traffic, and has a regression test that fills the default 64-buffer pool and verifies the full load/evict cycle.
- Added listener-review workflow: `my-claw/docs/listener-review.md` documents weekly review cadence, step-by-step rule ablation via the `senseweave-render-debugger` CLI (CCH-010), and how to attach review notes; `my-claw/sdp/review-log.md` provides a structured template with piece, date, felt_wrong, suspected_rule, ablation_result, and action fields; `render.listener_review` validates artifact integrity and anchors the documented CLI name to the live debugger parser.
- Added audio-rendered novelty verification for SenseWeave fixtures: `render.audio_novelty` now writes deterministic 5-minute proxy WAVs, extracts librosa mel-feature self-similarity matrices plus Foote novelty curves, aligns symbolic CCH-034 novelty peak times to audio peaks within 500 ms, and fails flattened synthesis even when symbolic metrics remain healthy.
- Coupled narrative engine to SectionEnvelope selection: new `narrative_envelope.py` module maps procedural arc state (phase, density, dynamic, timbre) and section function into populated SectionEnvelope instances with phase-shaped tension trajectories, tone-derived brightness and dynamic planes, and arc-driven density targets. `compose_score_tree()` now produces non-default section envelopes on every section node, so dramatic arcs drive section-level musical parameters instead of using flat defaults.
- Added the core SenseWeave render-ablation API: `senseweave.render.ablation.ablate()` now filters selected active render rule IDs, preserves remaining rule order, rerenders through an injected renderer, rejects unknown disabled IDs, and exposes a default no-rule path through the existing score-to-frequency renderer for future humanization tooling.
- Added operator diagnostics for production-course decisions: `operator_diagnostics.py` now extracts production-course chapter values (phase, scale/mode, harmonic function, groove, production strategy, mix role, spatial profile) from tracker runtime `scene_metadata` with fallback to score-tree sections; Theramini relation combines counterpoint relation with live Theramini playing state; critique notes derive threshold violations from ear-engine metrics; all three fields degrade gracefully to "unavailable" when authority files are absent or corrupt; `/status` display renders the new fields in the SenseWeave section.
- Added executable production-course curriculum exercises: `ExerciseSpec` now carries a runnable `template` and explicit `expected_features` while preserving the legacy `expected` alias; generated exercise specs include both metadata forms; and the EMSD curriculum now has verifier-backed exercises for intervals/scales, chord voicings, progressions, rhythm/groove, counterpoint, synthesis architecture, mix/master, SenseWeave mapping, Theramini ensemble, genre strategy, and full-arc production.
- Added course-driven self-critique and revision targets: `self_critique.py` now maps production-course chapter concepts (mode_scale, harmonic_function, meter_groove, counterpoint_relation, synthesis_architecture, mix_role, spatial_intent, genre_strategy, transition_type, phase_profile) to concrete ear-engine metric thresholds via `COURSE_METRIC_MAP`; `thresholds_for_course()` merges per-section course metadata into quality thresholds (stricter wins); `critique_score_with_course()` returns a `CourseCritiqueReport` with `CourseFailure` attribution naming the specific course concept behind each metric violation; `revision_targets_from_failures()` maps failures to `RevisionTargets` specifying which musical dimensions (form, harmony, rhythm, register, mix, strategy) are open for bounded revision without changing piece identity; `revise_score()` accepts an optional `course` kwarg; `tracker_compiler.py` and `duet_composer.py` fallback paths now pass section production_course to `revise_score`.
- Added SuperCollider recipe references for curriculum: created 22 discoverable recipe files in `my-claw/curriculum/recipes/supercollider/` for topics from MIDI-to-frequency to master-bus, linked them from EMSD-102 and EMSD-130 reference docs, and added static validation tests in `tests/test_supercollider_recipes.py` that check for required labels without coupling to the live audio server.
- Added dissonance/resolution metadata checks to counterpoint rules using music_theory.py interval consonance data: new `DissonanceAnnotation` and `DissonanceReport` dataclasses carry full `Interval` objects from the music theory library; `analyze_dissonance()` annotates each vertical interval in a voice-pair sequence with consonance classification and stepwise resolution status; `verify_resolution_sequence()` validates that all sharp dissonances resolve properly; `resolution_completeness_score()` returns a 0.0-1.0 ratio; and `weighted_voice_leading_smoothness()` penalizes unresolved dissonances in the smoothness metric.
- Added post-tonal, spectral, and microtonal material strategies: extended `music_theory.py` with `PitchClassSet`, `spectral_partials`, `quarter_tone_to_freq`, and `just_intonation_chord`; added `extract_spectral_peaks` to `audio_analysis.py` for SenseWeave seeding; and wired `harmonic_planner.py` to return avant-garde strategies when requested by phase/style.

- Added artistic identity portfolio reporting and surface snapshots: new `portfolio_report.py` module provides `derive_portfolio_report()` for comprehensive identity summaries from repertoire metrics, preferred forms/modes, motif counts, practice block coverage with EMSD course codes, growth-state keys, and ear quality averages; and `derive_surface_snapshot()` for face/operator display data (current song title, section caption, practice block, artistic-intent line). Graceful degradation handles empty repertoire, missing fields, corrupt score trees, and absent growth state without hallucinating data.
- Added installation-aware acoustic ecology policies: new `acoustic_ecology.py` module provides `resolve_acoustic_ecology()` which translates presence, cadence, day phase, room activity, attention state, and dwell time into a frozen `AcousticEcologyPolicy` with hard ceilings for volume, onset density, and spectral brightness, silence window parameters, ordered source preferences, keynote privilege weights, and density/voice caps. Sleep and wind-down modes enforce non-negotiable ceilings that cannot be overridden by any modifier. Performance attention overrides wind-down constraints when the human is actively engaged. Room activity boosts keynote privilege so the room's own soundscape is the acoustic content.
- Added live-buffer and sample-bank abstractions for SenseWeave inputs: new `live_buffer.py` module provides `LiveBuffer` for stable real-time environmental audio state (source name, capture path, freshness, RMS, spectral profile, transform history) and `SampleBankArchive` for retaining selected clips to archive storage with JSON metadata sidecars.
- Added pre-performance self-critique and bounded revision passes: new `self_critique.py` module provides `preview_score()` for offline metric analysis, `critique_score()` for threshold-based quality gating, and `revise_score()` for one bounded rewrite attempt that preserves piece identity (key, mood, tempo) while improving at least one failed metric.
- Tuned local SDP agent templates for dirty-baseline operation: leads must commit task-scoped changes, while verifiers now treat unrelated pre-existing dirty workspace state as notes instead of failing otherwise-correct tasks or asking agents to clean another operator's work.
- Implemented ST1-ST6 of the score-tree songwriting stack end to end: added `piece_commission.py`, `piece_brief.py`, `form_grammar.py`, `score_tree.py`, `recursive_composer.py`, `composition_gate.py`, `tracker_compiler.py`, and `piece_queue.py`; extended `repertoire_memory.py` to store structural score-tree summaries; and rewired `duet_composer.py` so tracker solo mode can commission a piece, build a complete score tree, gate it, compile it into tracker scenes, and precompose the next piece into a small persistent queue instead of treating the tracker as the composer.
- Rebalanced the first live score-tree pass for audibility: fresh post-restart commissions now avoid jumping straight to a maximal sparse suite unless the cadence is already wind-down/sleep-oriented, and `music_tracker_runtime.py` now emits stronger safe amplitudes for primary melody/bass/rhythm lanes so a healthy running piece is easier to hear and meter.
- Fixed the long-section tracker compile bug that was turning songs into isolated sustained tones: `tracker_compiler.py` now converts large section budgets into repeat counts plus modest note-length scaling, and `music_tracker.py` quantizes those repeats into real repeated phrase cycles instead of stretching a handful of notes across the whole scene.
- Finished the next score-tree composition pass: `tracker_compiler.py` now derives and enriches a fresh score per section, applies section-function and motif-aware phrase transforms before tracker quantization, and `music_tracker.py` now varies repeated cycles inside long sections, so longer pieces can develop through distinct section writing instead of only looping one shared phrase body.
- Added internal phrase-family development inside longer sections: `Phrase` now carries metadata, `tracker_compiler.py` expands section bodies into recursive families like `A`, `A_prime`, and `B`, and `music_tracker.py` annotates emitted steps with `internal_phrase_family` so development sections can be tested and diagnosed as more than literal loops.
- Coordinated those internal phrase families across tracker roles: shared root/function profiles now shape melody, bass, counter, and color variants together, and tracker steps expose `internal_family_root_degree` plus `internal_family_function` for diagnostics and future orchestration consumers.
- Added authored section transitions: `tracker_compiler.py` now tags each non-final scene with the next scene/function/root target, and `music_tracker.py` marks and retunes final-cycle tail steps as transition preparation so long sections aim into the following section instead of simply looping until a hard boundary.
- Added staged lane windows inside repeated tracker scenes: `music_tracker.py` now assigns per-role `entry_cycle` / `exit_cycle` metadata and delays counter/color support in long development-style sections, so sections can thicken internally instead of launching every lane at row 0.
- Fixed transition metadata through motif recall: recalled `Recap` / `Release` lanes now strip stale source-scene transition fields and attach the current scene's own transition target to their final preparation tail.
- Added section-level motif development and local harmonic progressions: `tracker_compiler.py` now labels each section as statement, sequence/fragment, contrast inversion, recall answer, liquidation, or residue, reshapes phrase material accordingly, and applies section-local progressions that are exposed on tracker scenes and steps for bass/progression verification.
- Added section-level rhythmic development: `tracker_compiler.py` now maps section functions to named rhythm cells such as steady statement, syncopated fragment, half-time displacement, recall groove, and residue breath, reshaping phrase durations/accents and exposing `rhythm_development` / `rhythm_cell` through tracker metadata.
- Fixed recalled motif rhythm metadata so later sections that borrow earlier material inherit the current scene's rhythm/progression profile instead of leaking the source scene's old `rhythm_development`.
- Added arrangement automation curves to tracker playback: `music_tracker.py` now derives `arrangement_curve` from section rhythm, writes row-point automation for `density`, `master_amp`, and `reverb_send`, shapes note velocity across each lane's active window, and `music_tracker_runtime.py` / `duet_composer.py` now expose and apply interpolated automation to the live master bus during the section. Low density also thins optional color/counter runtime events while preserving melody and bass continuity.
- Fixed a live capture fallback issue that made the sampler lean on a quiet self bus: `room_listener.py` now skips absent named JACK ports and tries direct `jack_rec` fallback ports such as `system:capture_1`, while `sample_dsp_activity.py` now resolves missing `theramini_in` to `contact_mic` / `room_mic` before `self_bus`.
- Rebalanced the live song mix after the repeat-cycle fix: `music_tracker_runtime.py` now gives texture lanes a stronger floor while slightly easing bass dominance, and `emsd_performance.py` now uses a gentler amp-scaling curve so normal `away_practice` songs no longer pin bass and melody at the top of the EMSD gain range.
- Fixed the live score-tree runtime on CypherClaw: `duet_composer.py` now derives commission context defensively from the world when `TrackerPlan` lacks `day_phase` / `weekly_phase`, `master_bus.py` now exposes an explicit `sw_master_smooth` seed helper, and `restart_composer.sh` now reseeds that master node again after the new composer PID is confirmed alive so the first piece does not run with scene-level `/n_set` traffic targeting a dead node.
- Added a concrete score-tree composition spec for the next songwriting pass: `cypherclaw-score-tree-composition-spec.md` now defines the piece commission layer, narrative brief contract, section-function grammar, score-tree data model, recursive composer, composition gate, tracker compiler, repertoire score-tree memory, and rollout phases needed to move CypherClaw from short tracker-first sketches toward longer, more varied composed pieces.
- Isolated observer vision from the shared local model queue: added `cypherclaw-observer-ollama.service` on `127.0.0.1:11435`, routed `observer_vision.py` to try `11435` before `11434`, and taught the multimodal call path to fail over across ordered observer Ollama URLs before dropping to local fallback mode.
- Moved heavy runtime storage toward the large archive volume: added `archive_paths.py`, taught `sample_playback_engine.py` and `archive_daemon.py` to resolve a shared archive root (preferring `/mnt/archive/cypherclaw` on the live box), updated `cypherclaw_boot.sh` to put porch/side capture rings on that archive root, and reconfigured the live host so Litestream observatory/state file replicas live off the root disk with a much tighter observatory snapshot retention window.
- Hardened the slow observer-vision path: `observer_vision.py` now treats Ollama `503 server busy / maximum pending requests exceeded` as queue saturation instead of a user-facing description, preserves the HTTP body detail in `vision_error`, emits a compact local fallback description with `vision_backend: \"local_fallback\"`, and backs off before retrying the multimodal model call again.
- Repaired the live display/camera contract on CypherClaw: `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now reapplies the observed dual-head layout (`DP-2` face at `1280x1024`, `DP-0` gallery at `3840x2160`) and launches face/gallery on `:0.0` / `:0.1`, while `gallery_x11.py` now uses origin positioning on the secondary X screen instead of the old combined-desktop offset that left the 4K monitor partially black.
- Hardened the local webcam path: `observer_vision.py` now defaults to `/dev/video0`, records `video_device`, and rejects stale old JPEGs when `ffmpeg` capture fails; `room_presence_daemon.py` can now run in `--observer-frame-only` mode and report `capture_source: "observer_frame"` so presence can share the single observer webcam instead of contending for it.
- Mirrored the shared observer frame back into `/tmp/room_frame.jpg` when `room_presence_daemon.py` is running in `--observer-frame-only` mode, so archive and room-frame consumers stay fresh instead of freezing on the last independent room-camera capture.
- Tightened the user-boot camera ownership path too: `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now deduplicates the local observer/presence daemons and starts `room_presence_daemon.py` in shared-observer mode, which prevents repeated boot invocations from piling up dozens of competing camera loops on the live box.
- Locked the EMSD room sampler to tracker transport: `sample_dsp_activity.py` now emits `transport_trigger_now` / `transport_trigger_key`, `sample_playback_engine.py` uses those keys to launch once per musical bucket instead of only by cooldown, and the face/status layer can now reflect that transport-synchronized sampler execution.
- Made the self-monitor more truthful: `self_listener.py` now derives glyph-facing brightness and motion from captured audio features instead of target-only metadata, while `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` pins the live meter to the verified JACK path on CypherClaw and still leaves PipeWire / `pw-jack` capture as fallback code paths.
- Fixed the remaining live self-monitor blackout path: when direct `jack_rec` capture times out, `self_listener.py` now falls back to analyzing a fresh `/tmp/room_capture.wav` clip instead of writing a dark `capture_timeout` state, so glyph and sampler decisions stay audio-derived on boxes where the JACK recorder hangs.
- Added real EMSD master-bus control: `master_bus.py` now translates live `mix_*` fields plus tracker-scene `master_amp` / `reverb_send` automation into `sw_master_smooth` `/n_set` updates at scene start, so EMSD mix intent now shapes the summed output path instead of only per-note rendering.
- Extended hook phrasing into actual later-section pitch behavior: `score_from_mood()` now publishes hook answer-degree metadata, and `music_tracker.py` uses that data in `Recap` / `Release` / `Resolution` / `Afterglow` so later sections can answer harmonically as well as textually.
- Collapsed split boot ownership for the core AV stack: `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now delegates audio/composer/face/gallery/room-listener/sample startup to `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh`, which keeps one authority for those daemons instead of racing duplicate boot paths.
- Added a replayable musical integration regression that exercises the composer-state -> sampler-plan -> sample-playback -> self-listener glyph state -> face-status chain, so this integration can be verified without a live host.
- Hardened the live audio runtime after the Scarlett/JACK outage: `start_audio.sh` now links the repo SynthDef bundle into `~/.local/share/SuperCollider/synthdefs`, starts `scsynth` with synthdef auto-load enabled, and prefers a real JACK/Scarlett graph before falling back to `pw-jack`; `restart_composer.sh` now restarts the composer gracefully and verifies the new PID instead of rebuilding synthdefs with `/d_recv`; and `cypherclaw_boot.sh` no longer blindly sends `/n_set` to master node `99999` after boot.
- Tightened that audio-runtime recovery again so `start_audio.sh` only stays on the real-JACK path when `system:playback_1` is actually present, and it now retries `scsynth` on `pw-jack` automatically if the real JACK graph disappears or never registers `SuperCollider:out_1`.
- Made the Scarlett recovery path deterministic: when real JACK needs to be rebuilt, `start_audio.sh` now clears stale JACK state, relaunches `jackdbus`, and configures the ALSA backend for `hw:USB` before starting `scsynth`, so the box can recover onto the Scarlett monitor path instead of drifting into a PipeWire-only fallback.
- Relaxed composer restart verification to the real steady-state condition: `restart_composer.sh` now waits for any healthy `duet_composer.py` process instead of only trusting the very first child PID, which avoids false failures during the current live startup race.
- Made the composer restart truly session-detached: `restart_composer.sh` now launches `duet_composer.py` with `nohup setsid ... </dev/null` so the live composer survives operator SSH/session teardown instead of disappearing with the parent shell.
- Added a persistent cold-boot path for the live AV runtime: `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now restarts `start_audio.sh`, `restart_composer.sh`, `self_listener.py`, `room_listener.py`, `sample_playback_engine.py`, and `face_display.py` under detached sessions, and `cypherclaw-av-stack.service` can bind that stack to `graphical.target` so music and the face monitor return after reboot without a manual SSH recovery.
- Tightened the cold-boot wrapper to avoid daemon duplication: it now waits for `SuperCollider:out_1` before launching the meter, and it only backfills `room_listener.py`, `sample_playback_engine.py`, and `face_display.py` if another startup source has not already brought them up during the same boot.
- Made the cold-boot wrapper opportunistic instead of combative: if `scsynth` and `duet_composer.py` are already present from another startup path, `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now skips `start_audio.sh` / `restart_composer.sh` entirely and only backfills the missing meter/listener surface.
- Made `self_listener.py` backend-aware: it now auto-selects between `jack_rec` and `pw-jack jack_rec`, sets `JACK_NO_START_SERVER=1` on its capture probes to avoid waking an unwanted JACK server, and publishes `capture_backend` in `/tmp/self_listen.json` so operators can tell which live graph the meter is following.
- Hardened that backend selection for the real CypherClaw boot race: direct `jack_lsp` probes can now take longer without forcing a false `pw-jack` fallback, `self_listener.py` caches the last working backend and resets that cache after failed capture loops, its `jack_rec` capture path now discards child stdout/stderr instead of risking a blocked pipe and stale meter state, and `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now deduplicates stale `room_listener.py`, `sample_playback_engine.py`, and `face_display.py` copies instead of letting old bad boot loops accumulate dozens of live daemons.
- Made the cold-boot meter less ambiguous: `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now chooses `SELF_LISTENER_CAPTURE_BACKEND` from the boot-time graph decision, preferring a live PipeWire sink monitor before JACK fallbacks, and it performs a second delayed dedupe pass so late-start room/sampler/face daemons from other boot hooks are collapsed back to one process each.
- Swapped the self-listener toward a host-stable monitor path: `self_listener.py` now prefers a PipeWire sink monitor target when one is available, still falls back to direct JACK or `pw-jack` port capture when needed, and keeps the old backend cache/reprobe logic only as fallback behavior instead of the primary live path.
- Brought the gallery back under the same AV boot contract as the face: the repo now ships a top-level `gallery_x11.py` entrypoint again, and `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now starts and deduplicates `gallery_x11.py` alongside `face_display.py` so reboot recovery cannot leave the gallery unmanaged or multiplied into dozens of stale X processes.
- Tightened the display recovery behavior again: `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now force-restarts `face_display.py` and `gallery_x11.py` on recovery instead of only deduplicating them, because a single stale headless display process was enough to leave the monitors blank while still looking “healthy” in `ps`.
- Fixed the display-runtime environment for those restarts too: `cypherclaw_av_boot.sh` now exports `XDG_RUNTIME_DIR=/run/user/1000` before launching face and gallery, which avoids the live SDL/X error where both display clients would restart with `DISPLAY=:0` but still fail to attach to the user session.
- Turned EMSD sample planning into real playback: added `sample_event_renderer.py`, `sample_playback_engine.py`, and `sample_status.py`; `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now starts the playback daemon; `/tmp/sample_dsp_activity.json` now feeds rendered room-derived WAV events through `pw-play`; and `/tmp/sample_playback_state.json` exposes the live sampler state for operators and face surfaces.
- Hardened the sample-playback daemon so stable ambient scenes can refresh repeatedly after cooldown instead of firing once per unchanged signature, and render failures now write a structured error state instead of crashing the loop.
- Taught `face_display.py` to surface the live EMSD sample layer from `/tmp/sample_dsp_activity.json`, so the head monitor can show which source and activity mode the room-sampling layer is currently holding or triggering.
- Rebalanced EMSD source authority toward the room in lived-in late phases: capstone `Convergence` and `Crystallization` now prefer `room_mic` outside `away_practice`, DSP scene focus follows that same room bias, and `sample_dsp_activity.py` can retarget a sparse late-phase `self_bus` request onto a fresh room capture while still preserving the original requested source in state for operator visibility.
- Fixed room-capture triggering so external sample sources no longer depend on `self_listener` RMS. `room_mic`, `contact_mic`, and `theramini_in` now trigger from their own live cues, while only `self_bus` remains gated by self-audio level.
- Tightened head-monitor truth again: the sample status line can now read `/tmp/sample_playback_state.json` and show actual live sampler playback instead of only the planned source/mode.
- Made the sampler musically scene-aware instead of only transform-aware: `sample_dsp_activity.py` now emits scene profiles like `development_grains`, `theme_accents`, `recap_echo`, `divination_bed`, and `afterglow_residue`, and `sample_event_renderer.py` now changes duration, density, peak target, filtering, stretch, and echo geometry from those profiles so the room layer follows the tracker form instead of using one generic behavior under different labels.
- Promoted the Perform-VE room mic to the actual live capture path: `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now starts `room_listener.py` without `--no-jack`, and `room_listener.py` now reports `capture_backend` / `capture_source` so the live state shows whether JACK on the condenser path or an ALSA fallback is in use.
- Adjusted room-listener fallback priority so ALSA auto-selection now prefers the Perform-VE interface over webcam or generic analog capture when JACK is unavailable.
- Made room-listener ALSA capture more resilient by retrying alternate sample formats on each candidate device before falling through to the next one.
- Made Perform-VE usable through the Linux audio stack by teaching `room_listener.py` to prefer a PipeWire `pw-record` target for Perform-VE before trying JACK or ALSA fallbacks.
- Rebased the EMSD ambient default onto the real room condenser path: Divination/capstone planning and DSP source focus now prefer `room_mic` instead of `garden_mic`, so the default ambient sampler matches the Perform-VE microphone actually present on CypherClaw.
- Made EMSD sample activity resilient to missing sources: `sample_dsp_activity.py` can now resolve a requested source like `garden_mic` onto a fresh room/contact/self capture when the requested alias is unavailable, and `self_listener.py` now publishes a full capture registry so that fallback can happen from live file freshness instead of hardcoded guesswork.
- Wired stable EMSD sample capture into the live runtime: added `capture_alias.py` plus `sample_dsp_activity.py`, taught `room_listener.py`, `contact_listener.py`, `theramini_listener.py`, and `self_listener.py` to mirror fresh clips into `/tmp/room_capture.wav`, `/tmp/contact_capture.wav`, `/tmp/theramini_capture.wav`, and `/tmp/self_capture.wav`, and made `self_listener.py` publish `/tmp/sample_dsp_activity.json` with concrete activity modes, trigger flags, and DSP/sample-control values derived from composer, cadence, and sensor state.
- Expanded CypherClaw boot coverage for the EMSD sampler path: `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now starts `theramini_listener.py` and `contact_listener.py` alongside the room listener so the stable sample aliases can refresh during unattended startup instead of remaining planned-but-missing files.
- Fed EMSD production plans into actual tracker playback: added `emsd_performance.py`, wired `duet_composer.py` to apply live mix/sample/DSP adjustments at the note boundary, extended `composer_emsd_extras()` with concrete sample capture metadata, and made the strongest top register fold down harder so notes above roughly `C6` are lowered an octave and the sharpest band is lowered two octaves.
- Wired the next EMSD runtime pass into live state: added `emsd_runtime.py`, taught `duet_composer.py` to build a typed EMSD context per tracker song and publish arc/mix/sample/DSP/identity fields into `/tmp/composer_state.json`, extended `repertoire_memory.py` to retain `patch_name`, and taught `self_listener.py` to publish `/tmp/glyph_audio_features.json` by combining live audio analysis with composer/cadence state for GlyphWeave-facing consumers.
- Built the first end-to-end EMSD package: added a 40-course curriculum catalog plus generated `my-claw/curriculum/EMSD-*` scaffolds, and implemented `sound_palette_lab.py`, `sample_lab.py`, `mix_engine.py`, `procedural_arc.py`, `dsp_scene_lab.py`, `artistic_identity.py`, and `capstone_engine.py` so the electronic music production roadmap now exists as runnable code and tests instead of only a brief.
- Folded the highest live octave down by one octave at playback time: `voice_shaping.py` now marks the extreme top band with a `pitch_multiplier`, and `play_voice()` applies that fold before sending OSC so CypherClaw's brightest instruments stop landing in the most painful register.
- Tightened title-hook coherence again: `hook_engine.py` now chooses title phrases from image-field-aware pools that also react to cadence, progression profile, hook type, and repertoire source titles, so CypherClaw can move between labels like `Low Light`, `Electric Circuits`, `Moving Lines`, and `Open Thresholds` without collapsing back to generic or repeated adjective-noun pairs.
- Very high-note playback shaping is now stronger and more explicit: `voice_shaping.py` emits best-effort `highpass_hz` and `saturation_mix` controls in addition to the existing top-octave gain/brightness/release shaping, and `play_voice()` forwards those controls so ear-splitting notes can be filtered and driven slightly when the live SynthDefs support it.
- Tightened hook-language quality at the source: `hook_engine.py` now normalizes rough historical phrases like `carry the line wide` and `open the room open`, and `repertoire_memory.py` repairs those forms on load/store so they stop resurfacing through recall.
- Made face captions orchestration-aware: `prosody_engine.py` now uses `patch_name` and lane count so sparse scenes compress hook language while denser scenes widen it into fuller face text.
- Made face captions harmonic-function-aware: `prosody_engine.py` now uses `cadence_type` for `Resolution` and `Afterglow`, so the same hook can resolve differently under dominant, plagal, authentic, and deceptive harmonic landings.
- Added legacy repertoire hook repair: `repertoire_memory.py` now normalizes broken historical hook text like `answer the again` on load and store, so old artifacts stop leaking into new songs and captions.
- Made scene captions section-aware: `prosody_engine.py` now reshapes the same hook differently for `Theme`, `Recap`/`Release`, and `Resolution`/`Afterglow`, so face text follows the song arc instead of repeating one caption verbatim.
- Made repertoire answer hooks less literal and less repetitive: `hook_engine.py` now chooses among contextual phrase-level answer variants based on family/cadence/song state, so recalled hook lines stay grammatical without collapsing into one stock response.
- Tightened repertoire hook language and payoff shaping: answer-mode hooks now use phrase-level transforms instead of awkward generic suffixes, repertoire memory can target a preferred payoff scene, and tracker runtime state now exposes scene metadata like `payoff_focus` for live correlation.
- Extended repertoire influence into tracker form memory: the live composer can now inherit a prior strong song's preferred progression profile, title/hook recall mode, form variant, and section-density bias before building the next tracker song.
- Made repertoire memory active instead of archival-only: `repertoire_memory.py` now returns forward-looking influence by family/cadence, `hook_engine.py` can answer or recall prior title/hook material, and the live composer can bias the next song's progression profile before score generation begins.
- Built the first complete M1-M6 musicianship package end to end: added `reharmonizer.py`, `hook_engine.py`, `arrangement_engine.py`, `ear_engine.py`, `practice_curriculum.py`, `prosody_engine.py`, and `repertoire_memory.py`; extended `harmonic_planner.py`, `generative_scores.py`, `music_tracker.py`, `continuous_learner.py`, `duet_composer.py`, and `keyboard_chat.py` so tracker songs now carry section functions, cadence types, hook metadata, scene arrangement intent, practice-block focus, ear-metric evaluation, repertoire storage, and face-visible song titles/captions through the live runtime.
- Added `docs/cypherclaw-musicianship-roadmap.md`, which maps the Berklee songwriting curriculum onto CypherClaw's live harmony, melody, arrangement, ear-training, practice, and repertoire systems, and linked it from the upgrade checklist as the next musicianship program after stability work.
- Lowered the live bass register further, widened per-patch octave spacing across bass/melody/counter/color, and made that register policy survive the whole tracker pipeline by preserving patch metadata through family shaping, cadence clamping, tracker scene building, and runtime scheduling.
- Broke the fixed tracker-song mold: `tracker_form_for_family(..., song_num=...)` now yields variant forms with different scene counts and scene-length multipliers, so CypherClaw no longer plays every song with the same five-scene duration profile.
- Added a small high-note saturation-style shaping layer for live playback. Because the current synths do not expose a true drive parameter, very high notes are softened by trimming gain/release, reducing pluck brightness, and adding a little detune/space instead of sending unsupported OSC args.

